  "text": "Quantum physics allows us a perfect randomness, so most of all quantum information-theoretic primitives try to offer an unconditional security under the randomness. For examples, quantum key distribution protocols such as BB84 [CITATION_1] and B92 [CITATION_2] highly depend on a random measurements for given classified non-orthogonal quantum states.",
